data.content:
Yes — MSTest v3.3+ supports **typed test data** via generic `TestDataRow<T>`, eliminating the `object[]` boxing:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<TestDataRow<string, bool>> TestData =>
[
    new("valid@email.com", true),
    new("invalid", false),
    new("", false),
];
```

**Key differences:**

- `TestDataRow<string, bool>` replaces `object[]` — arguments are type-checked at compile time
- `[TestData]` replaces `[DynamicData]`
- No more silent runtime `InvalidCastException` if you mix up parameter types

Requires **MSTest 3.3+** (`MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.Sdk`).
